<title>Step 2: Keyboard Layout</title>
<simpara role="RHC.DUMMY">
  </simpara>
<para role="RHC.\h1"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_1\img" fileref="kmtitlelogo.gif" depth="33" width="33" align="left"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>Step 2: Layout</para>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">1.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_2\span">            </phrase> Select the <inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_3\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image018.jpg" depth="39" width="42"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject> tab.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p">The Design your keyboard layout screen is displayed:</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_4\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image020.jpg" depth="441" width="622"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.\h2">The Layout Screen</para>
<!--(Table)=========================================================-->

  <informaltable frame="none"><tgroup colsep="0" rowsep="0" role="RHC.rml10_5__Tavultesoft\table" cols="2"><colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/><colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/><tbody><row role="RHC.rml10_6\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_7\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Character Set:</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_8\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">The selected character set chosen on the Details tab.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_9\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_10\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Font:</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_11\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">Displays the selected font for the keyboard. Click on the link to change.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_12\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_13\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Keyboard</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_14\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">The QWERTY keyboard is displayed.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_15\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_16\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Key:</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_17\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">Display the selected key on the keyboard and any combinations with the Shift, Ctrl and Alt keys.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_18\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_19\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Distinguish between left and right Ctrl/Alt</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_20\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">Allows the users to have more combinations or to leave the left Ctrl and Alt keys for general keyboard shortcuts, for example Copy and Paste.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_21\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_22\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Display 102nd Key</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_23\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">European keyboards have a 102nd key.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_24\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_25\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Unicode Character Value(s)</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_26\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">The Unicode value for the assigned key.</para>
      </entry>
    </row><row role="RHC.rml10_27\tr">
      <entry role="RHC.rml10_28\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Output character(s)</phrase></para>
      </entry>

      <entry role="RHC.rml10_29\td">
        <para role="RHC.TableContents\p">The output character that will be displayed when the key is selected on the keyboard.</para>
      </entry>
    </row></tbody></tgroup></informaltable>

  <para role="RHC.\h2">Changing the font</para>

  <para role="RHC.\p">Click on the <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Font</phrase> link <inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_30\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image022.jpg" depth="16" width="103"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject> and select the required font</para>

  <para role="RHC.\h2">Assigning characters to keys</para>

  <para role="RHC.\p">There are two ways to assign characters to the keys:</para>

  <itemizedlist role="RHC.rml10_31\ul">
    <listitem role="RHC.kadov-p-CBulletedPoint\li"><para role="RHC.BulletedPoint\p">Typing in a <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Character Code</phrase></para></listitem>

    <listitem role="RHC.kadov-p-CBulletedPoint\li"><para role="RHC.BulletedPoint\p">Dragging and dropping from the <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Character Map</phrase></para></listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para role="RHC.TIP\p"><phrase role="RHC.rml10_32\span">è</phrase>      Any key that does not have a character assigned to it will work as usual.</para>

  <para role="RHC.\h3">Character Code</para>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">1.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_33\span">            </phrase> Select the letter on the design keyboard.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_34\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image024.jpg" depth="45" width="45"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">2.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_35\span">            </phrase> In the <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Unicode value(s)</phrase> field enter the Unicode value.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_36\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image026.jpg" depth="21" width="315"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p">When the value is recognized an output value will be displayed.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_37\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image028.jpg" depth="26" width="315"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p">The letter will now display two characters.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_38\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image030.jpg" depth="45" width="44"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.\h3"><anchor id="CharacterMap"/>Character Map</para>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">1.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_39\span">            </phrase> From the <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">View</phrase> menu select <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Character Map</phrase></para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p">The Character Map is displayed on the right hand side of the screen.</para>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">2.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_40\span">            </phrase> Select the required block, for example Basic Latin or Latin 1 - Extended.</para>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">3.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_41\span">            </phrase> Select the letter on the keyboard and double click on the character in the character map.</para>

  <para role="RHC.rml10_42__Inlinedented\p"><phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">OR</phrase></para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p">Click and hold on the character and drag and drop on to the letter on the keyboard.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_43\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image032.jpg" depth="57" width="112"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>        <inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_44\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image034.jpg" depth="43" width="44"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.Indented\p">The key value is displayed</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_45\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image036.jpg" depth="64" width="468"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p">The Unicode value and output value is displayed.</para>

  <para role="RHC.Picture\p"><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_46\img" fileref="Project%20-%20Keyboard%20Component_files/image038.jpg" depth="58" width="475"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para role="RHC.Tip\p"><phrase role="RHC.rml10_47\span">è</phrase>      To add the character to a key with existing characters, hold <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Ctrl</phrase> while dropping it onto the key.</para>

  <para role="RHC.InlineNormal1\p">Each key can:</para>

  <itemizedlist role="RHC.rml10_48\ul">
    <listitem role="RHC.kadov-p-CBulletedPoint\li"><para role="RHC.BulletedPoint\p"><phrase role="RHC.rml10_49\span"><phrase role="RHC.rml10_50\span"><!--kadov_tag{{<spaces>}}--> </phrase></phrase><!--kadov_tag{{</spaces>}}-->Have zero or more characters assigned to it.</para></listitem>

    <listitem role="RHC.kadov-p-CBulletedPoint\li"><para role="RHC.BulletedPoint\p">Be assigned a different set of characters for each shift state.</para></listitem>

    <listitem role="RHC.kadov-p-CBulletedPoint\li"><para role="RHC.BulletedPoint\p">Change the shift state by clicking on the Shift, Ctrl, and Alt keys.</para></listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para role="RHC.NumberedPoint\p">4.<phrase role="RHC.rml10_51\span">            </phrase> Click on the <phrase role="RHC.Bold\span">Save</phrase> button.</para>

  <para role="RHC.\h3">Filter</para>

  <para role="RHC.\p">The Filter allows a user to reduce the number of characters displayed in the character map. <!--kadov_tag{{<spaces>}}--> <!--kadov_tag{{</spaces>}}-->The standard filter options used are by font name or block name.</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem role="RHC.kadov-P-CBULLETEDPOINT\li"><para role="RHC.BULLETEDPOINT\p">Click on the <inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata role="RHC.rml10_52\img" fileref="image7.gif" depth="17" width="18"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject> to display the filter options.</para></listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

